The BigPic Morning Brief for Thursday, June 25, 2026 is written to `/home/bigpic/projects/bigpic-markets/morning-brief/2026-06/2026-06-25_Thu.md` — full HEAVY-load depth (~2,600 words), every figure sourced from the briefing file with no fabricated actuals (all 8:30 ET releases correctly marked Pending).

**The setup in three lines:**
- **Tech-led melt-up, gated by 8:30 PCE.** Nasdaq futures +2.01% (vs. S&P +0.61%, Dow +0.17%) on Micron's +17.48% blowout; Asia ripped (Kospi +5.42%, Nikkei +4.61% on the SK Hynix memory read-through). But Core PCE (consensus +0.3% vs. +0.2% prior) is a binary risk — a 0.4%+ print revives rate-hike chatter.
- **Watchlist saturation.** 14 of 17 pre-market >3% movers are thesis names, all green and AI/semi-aligned (MU, GLW, MRVL, ASML, AMD, CRWV, VRT, CGNX, TER, IBM, FLNC, BE). Meanwhile defense/space/minerals are washed out (LDOS RSI 19, NOC 31, PL 32, LUNR 33, ALB 35) despite bullish catalysts — a notable divergence.
- **Structural overlay flagged:** post-Triple-Witch bearish window (Jun 22–26) plus tomorrow's Russell Reconstitution (~$100B flows, material for the many small/mid-cap watchlist names).

I noted the internal tension worth respecting: futures are ripping but SPY trend reads bearish with only "moderate" risk appetite and VIX under-hedged into the data — so I framed the bias as cautiously bullish but explicitly two-sided on the 8:30 print, with bull/bear scenarios and the cross-asset confirm/deny gauges (10Y, DXY, VIX). Data caveats (FRED timeout, GLW anomaly being a real move) are surfaced rather than smoothed over.
